definition.value: A sialotetraosylceramide consisting of a branched hexasaccharide made up from two sialyl residues, two galactose residues, one N-acetylgalactosamine residue and a glucose residue at the reducing end attached to the ceramide portion via a beta-linkage.
A 20-carbon, methyl-branched hydroxy fatty acid and intermediate in phytanic acid degradation; accumulates in patients with peroxisimal disorders.
